<item>
            <title>[LU-18355] rolling-downgrade-client2 sanity test_56ei: Did not find any entries with expected projid 1234</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18355</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0f26ee9e-e966-4059-83c1-873622ea7f36&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0f26ee9e-e966-4059-83c1-873622ea7f36&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_56ei failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lfs: failed to set xattr for &apos;/mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/file1234&apos;: Operation not supported
lfs: failed to set xattr for &apos;/mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/link1234&apos;: Operation not supported
lfs: failed to set xattr for &apos;/mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/char1234&apos;: Operation not supported
    0 - /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity//char1234
    0 - /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity//file0
    0 - /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity//link1234
    0 - /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity//file1234
Actual output:
0 /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity
0 /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/char1234
0 /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/file0
0 /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/link1234
0 /mnt/lustre/d56ei.sanity/file1234
found_count: 0
 sanity test_56ei: @@@@@@ FAIL: Did not find any entries with expected projid 1234 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4582&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4582&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.27.1.el8_8.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4582&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4582&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.27.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The full test session versions show that client2 is running 2.12.9, which is expected given the test session:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Nodes: 	

    onyx-78vm4 - Client 1 (2.16.0.RC1, x86_64)
    onyx-78vm5 - Client 2 (2.12.9, x86_64)
    onyx-78vm6 - OST 1, OST 2, OST 3, OST 4, OST 5, OST 6, OST 7 (2.16.0.RC1, x86_64)
    onyx-78vm12 - MDS 1 (2.16.0.RC1, x86_64)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like rolling-downgrade-client2 is running the wrong test scripts for the Lustre version installed on the node?  In this case, test_56ei is being run on the client, but this subtest was only added in v2_15_64-110-g501e5b2c8a and does not exist on 2.12.9 clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, it looks like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs project -p&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is trying to call an interface to set the xattr on a special file, but that doesn&apos;t exist in older clients?&lt;/p&gt;







&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity test_56ei - Did not find any entries with expected projid 1234&lt;/p&gt;</description>
